{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f1b538e5-c575-4e8c-9231-4276842b890e","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019Pv5nzDt9Kphwvbu8QwPxC","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing K8s crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"b5877952-eb29-444a-9987-6e93c3399e49","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide them with the necessary configuration.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory). Types: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - specifies the output path and filename pattern for dumps\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - optional flag for debugging the createdump tool itself\n\nFor NativeAOT apps, I need to set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath=/opt/tools/createdump` to point to the custom location since the runtime won't have it bundled by default.\n\nActually, let me clarify the environment variables more carefully. CoreCLR uses `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType`, and `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` for crash dumps. NativeAOT in .NET 8+ also supports crash dumps through createdump and uses the same environment variable configuration, though it requires explicit setup since the tool isn't bundled with the runtime.\n\nFor the user's case with createdump at `/opt/tools/createdump`, they need to set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath=/opt/tools/createdump`. In Kubernetes, they'll also need a writable volume for the dump files, appropriate resource limits since dumps can be large, and the `SYS_PTRACE` capability so createdump can use ptrace to capture the process state.","outputTokens":710,"requestId":"6091:3AB79D:2D802A:3B2055:69FFE3D7"},"id":"fdda0ecf-c8e6-4e62-af5e-b2f2911ddddf","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:48:26.018Z","parentId":"397d043d-168f-47f2-88b4-622ba6b68ff5"}
