{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c4b2ee7-0062-4b1d-8344-08700f7d1a4a","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** for your container:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # Non-default createdump location\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — you need a writable volume for dumps and `SYS_PTRACE` (required by `createdump` to attach to the crashing process):\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dump-volume\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dump-volume\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 4Gi        # adjust based on expected app memory\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `SYS_PTRACE` is mandatory — without it `createdump` silently fails.\n- `MiniDumpType: 4` gives full memory dumps (best for debugging, but large). Use `2` (Heap) for a smaller alternative.\n- Set `sizeLimit` on the `emptyDir` to avoid node disk pressure from large dumps.\n- To debug `createdump` itself, add `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1`.\n- Consider a persistent volume or sidecar to exfiltrate dumps before pod eviction, since `emptyDir` is ephemeral.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b5877952-eb29-444a-9987-6e93c3399e49","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"6083:32FC8B:2F7E08:3D2B65:69FFE3E9"},"id":"10bf826f-efaa-4ba1-9d4a-91689ed225f2","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:48:35.779Z","parentId":"233b4a35-44d3-4e94-b2e5-5225be19aecf"}
